'''Joel McNeely''' composed the musical [[Shadows of the Empire (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for the ''[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]'' multimedia project. 

==Biography==
McNeely wrote the music for two other [[Lucasfilm]] productions: the [[1992]] television series ''[[w:c:indianajones:The_Young_Indiana_Jones_Chronicles|The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles]]'' and the [[1994]] feature film [[Wikipedia:Radioland Murders|''Radioland Murders'']].<ref name="shadows">''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]''</ref>

McNeely was hired to compose the musical [[Shadows of the Empire (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for the ''[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]'' multimedia project, according to which he took a classical approach. The soundtrack would accompany the storyline of [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|a book]] storyline instead of a movie. [[Robert Townson]] met with him to discuss the storyline's mood and grandeur, the dominant themes and agreed on what had to be composed. He also provided him with concept art by [[Ralph McQuarrie]].<ref name="shadows" /> 

In the spring of [[1996]] McNeely traveled to Scotland to conduct the [[Royal Scottish National Orchestra]] for the ''Shadows'' soundtrack.<ref name="shadows" /> Some of his compositions are heard in the soundtrack for the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Shadow of the Empire'' computer game]].<ref name="Game">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Shadow of the Empire'']]</ref>

